text.section:
A public official may offer to the Archives or may destroy any of the following materials that the public official no longer needs:
a book, magazine, or newspaper;
other library or museum material that was made or acquired for reference or exhibition purposes;
an extra copy of a document that was kept only for convenience of reference;
a stock of publications;
an acceptance or refusal of an invitation or engagement of a public officer; and
material that otherwise relates to personal business of a public officer.
